//Nested if Statement

Syntax:

if (condition1) {

// Executes if condition1 is true

if (condition2) {

// Executes if condition2 is true (inside the first if block)

} else {

// Executes if condition2 is false (inside the first if block)

}

} else {

// Executes if condition1 is false

}

The use of nested if statements in C programming allows you to evaluate multiple conditions in a hierarchical or
dependent manner. This is particularly useful when a decision needs to be made based on more than one
condition, where the outcome of the second (or subsequent)
